I really think that VI needs to fix the damn bug with factions in there anyway. You know the one I'm talking about.... The CoV faction mobs TELL you to go into the Hall of Testing and kill things but if they actually SEE or &quot;hear&quot; you doing it they turn around and kill YOU. Shouldn't they actually HELP??<br>
<br>
Today we took 2 groups to HoT because there was nothing much else to do. Our plan was to stay just inside the door and kill for a few hours. We didn't have any Shamen online and so didn't really have the force to go deeper. <br>
<br>
We got wiped about 5 times. There were other guilds in HoT and their late arrivial idiots kept opening the door on us. I doubt it was intentional as they were killing deeper inside and so had little interest in the mobs we were hunting. We were actually a help because we were protecting their backs.<br>
<br>
This problem IS a faction issue. The mobs that were wipeing us out were ALLY to us. Their faction wants us to fight where and what we were fighting. Why do they attack us when we are doing them a FAVOR??<br>
<br>
Hell yes I'm quite willing for the poster's proposal to go both ways. I'm tired of Oobah guilds effectively blocking the progress of those below by killing anything that will let them advance. If they want to kill +CoV mobs they should have to work for the right by changing their faction. I'm willing to work for the right to kill -CoV mobs.<br>
<br>
If they HAD to change their faction then they would be required to spend the week actually changing their faction. If they're busy doing that perhaps they'll be so busy that some other content will be left up for some one else to kill. <p>Runehammer Trollsbane<BR>
